# First story
*If you haven't seen [Introduction](Introduction) yet, read it first.*

To make your first story, you have to do some simple steps:
1. Add a new dialog using the button with plus sign below Story Tree.
	![Add button](data:image/png;base64,)
2. Type something onto it, be creative!
	![Dialog content](data:image/png;base64,)
3. Check *Is start dialog*
	![Start checked](data:image/png;base64,)
4. Create second dialog the same way as first one, **but don't select *Is start dialog*!**
5. Select first dialog, either on Tree or Diagram.
	![Select dialog](data:image/png;base64,)
6. Press button with plus in box, bottom right corner of the Story Tree. It will add new dialog option.
	![Add dialog button](data:image/png;base64,)
7. You know what to do. *(put some content)*
8. Double click *Target*.
	![Target](data:image/png;base64,)
9. Select second dialog **on Diagram**. Tree can help you navigate, as selecting item on Story Tree zooms Diagram onto it.
	![Select target](data:image/png;base64,)
10. Your first Story is complete!
